						<div class="postbody">I found this one tutorial quite interesting: <a href="http://www.strille.net/tutorials/part1_scrolling.php" class="postlink">http://www.strille.net/tutorials/part1_scrolling.php</a>
<br />
<br />It talks only about scrolling and updating the level map, but this is one of the most important things in a platformer. The maps are object-based, like in SMB1. All the code is for Flash (a very old version of it, actually), but the concepts still apply.
<br />
<br />Another thing you could do is look at some <a href="http://www.vplanetmag.com/mysite4.shtml" class="postlink">QBasic games</a>. This is how I learned the most about how games work. These games usually come with source, and Basic code is usually easy to read, much more so than 6502 assembly. Just keep in mind that some of the games are not very well structured.</div>

